      <hedline>
        <hl1>R.I. Biking</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Anne Connor letter on Daisann McLane's September 3 travel article describes other places to bike to on Rhode Island; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Daisann McLane discovered what the ''locals'' have long known -- the pleasures of riding the East Bay Bicycle Path along Narragansett Bay (''A Ramble, Without  a Car, Through Rhode Island,''  Sept. 3).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: Daisann McLane discovered what the ''locals'' have long known -- the pleasures of riding the East Bay Bicycle Path along Narragansett Bay (''A Ramble, Without  a Car, Through Rhode Island,''  Sept. 3).</p>
        <p>Some other options include Quito's, a lobster shack at the end of the bike path, and Swanson House, a quiet bed-and-breakfast on Ferry Road, both in Bristol. Midway on the bike path is the Daily Scoop at County Road in Barrington, for homemade ice cream, or Parvenue at Market Street in Warren, for irresistible desserts. We are proud of our bike path and use it.</p>
        <p>ANNE CONNOR  Providence, R.I.</p>
      </block>
